#. <section class="sutta" id="mn59"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn59:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 59"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 59"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn59:0.2"
msgid "Bahuvedanīyasutta"
msgstr "The Many Kinds of Feeling"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.397"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn59:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

#. VAR: thapati → gahapati (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn59:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho "
"pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga went up to Venerable Udāyī, bowed, sat "
"down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn59:1.4"
msgid "“kati nu kho, bhante udāyi, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, how many feelings has the Buddha spoken of?”"

msgctxt "mn59:1.5"
msgid "“Tisso kho, thapati, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“Master builder, the Buddha has spoken of three feelings:"

msgctxt "mn59:1.6"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "mn59:1.7"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha has spoken of these three feelings.”"

msgctxt "mn59:1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "mn59:1.9"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;"
msgstr "“Sir, Udāyī, the Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings."

msgctxt "mn59:1.10"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "He’s spoken of two feelings:"

msgctxt "mn59:1.11"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant and painful."

msgctxt "mn59:1.12"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha said that neutral feeling is included as a peaceful and subtle "
"kind of pleasure.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga:"

msgctxt "mn59:2.2"
msgid "“na kho, gahapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;"
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,"

msgctxt "mn59:2.3"
msgid "tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.”"

msgctxt "mn59:2.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:2.5"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:2.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "mn59:2.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;"
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings,"

msgctxt "mn59:2.8"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.”"

msgctxt "mn59:2.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:2.10"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga:"

msgctxt "mn59:3.2"
msgid "“na kho, thapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;"
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,"

msgctxt "mn59:3.3"
msgid "tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.”"

msgctxt "mn59:3.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:3.5"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:3.6"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "mn59:3.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā, "
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings, "

msgctxt "mn59:3.8"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.”"

msgctxt "mn59:3.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:3.10"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:3.11"
msgid ""
"Neva kho sakkhi āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ saññāpetuṃ, na panāsakkhi "
"pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ saññāpetuṃ."
msgstr "But neither was able to persuade the other."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.398"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:4.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ "
"imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Udāyī and Pañcakaṅga."

msgctxt "mn59:4.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "mn59:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi āyasmato udāyissa "
"pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed."

msgctxt "mn59:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:5.1"
msgid ""
"“santaññeva kho, ānanda, pariyāyaṃ pañcakaṅgo thapati udāyissa nābbhanumodi, "
"santaññeva ca pana pariyāyaṃ udāyī pañcakaṅgassa thapatissa nābbhanumodi."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, the explanation by the mendicant Udāyī, which the master builder "
"Pañcakaṅga didn’t agree with, was quite correct. But the explanation by "
"Pañcakaṅga, which Udāyī didn’t agree with, was also quite correct."

msgctxt "mn59:5.2"
msgid ""
"Dvepānanda, vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, tissopi vedanā vuttā mayā "
"pariyāyena, pañcapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chapi vedanā vuttā mayā "
"pariyāyena, aṭṭhārasapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chattiṃsapi vedanā "
"vuttā mayā pariyāyena, aṭṭhasatampi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""
"In one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another explanation I’ve "
"spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-six, or a hundred "
"and eight feelings."

msgctxt "mn59:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways."

msgctxt "mn59:5.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ na samanujānissanti na samanumaññissanti na samanumodissanti "
"tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ "
"mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissanti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or "
"agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, "
"continually wounding each other with barbed words."

msgctxt "mn59:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways."

msgctxt "mn59:5.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ samanujānissanti samanumaññissanti samanumodissanti tesametaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ "
"piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissanti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree "
"with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each "
"other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each "
"other with kindly eyes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:6.1"
msgid "Pañca kho ime, ānanda, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "mn59:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "mn59:6.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn59:6.4"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …"
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "mn59:6.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … pe …"
msgstr "Smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "mn59:6.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …"
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn59:6.7"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—"
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "mn59:6.8"
msgid "ime kho, ānanda, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "mn59:6.9"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, ānanda, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ "
"vuccati kāmasukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation is called sensual pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi."
msgstr ""
"There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and "
"happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that."

msgctxt "mn59:7.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn59:7.3"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:7.4"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:7.5"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi … pe … "
"paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "mn59:7.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.399"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi."
msgstr ""
"There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and "
"happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that."

msgctxt "mn59:8.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn59:8.3"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:8.4"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:8.5"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, "
"a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the "
"rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, "
"and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. …"

msgctxt "mn59:8.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:9.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:9.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:9.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:9.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains "
"in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and "
"aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ …"

msgctxt "mn59:9.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:10.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:10.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:10.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:10.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. …"

msgctxt "mn59:10.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:11.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:11.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:11.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:11.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā, paṭighasaññānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā, nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the "
"ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of "
"diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite space. …"

msgctxt "mn59:11.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:12.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:12.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:12.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:12.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’"
"ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, "
"aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension "
"of infinite consciousness. …"

msgctxt "mn59:12.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:13.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:13.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:13.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:13.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti "
"ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in "
"the dimension of nothingness. …"

msgctxt "mn59:13.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.400"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:14.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn59:14.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr "There is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:14.3"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:14.4"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, "
"enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn59:14.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:15.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi."
msgstr ""
"There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and "
"happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that."

msgctxt "mn59:15.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn59:15.3"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "mn59:15.4"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "mn59:15.5"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of neither "
"perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of "
"perception and feeling."

msgctxt "mn59:15.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:16.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "mn59:16.2"
msgid "‘saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samaṇo gotamo āha; tañca sukhasmiṃ paññapeti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama spoke of the cessation of perception and feeling, and he "
"includes it in happiness."

msgctxt "mn59:16.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ kiṃsu, tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti?"
msgstr "What’s up with that?’"

msgctxt "mn59:16.4"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, ānanda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "When wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them:"

msgctxt "mn59:16.5"
msgid ""
"‘na kho, āvuso, bhagavā sukhaṃyeva vedanaṃ sandhāya sukhasmiṃ paññapeti;"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, when the Buddha describes what’s included in happiness, he’s not "
"just referring to pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "mn59:16.6"
msgid ""
"api ca, āvuso, yattha yattha sukhaṃ upalabbhati yahiṃ yahiṃ taṃ taṃ "
"tathāgato sukhasmiṃ paññapetī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One describes pleasure as included in happiness wherever it’s "
"found, and in whatever context.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn59:16.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn59:16.8"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn59:16.9"
msgid "Bahuvedanīyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
